SIMPLE: pulchritude
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pulchritude
<hw>Pul"chri*tude</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pulchritudo</ets>, fr. <ets>pulcher</ets> beautiful.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>That quality of appearance which pleases the eye;
beauty; comeliness; grace; loveliness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Piercing our heartes with thy <qex>pulchritude</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Court of Love.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Attractive moral excellence; moral beauty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By the <qex>pulchritude</qex> of their souls make up what is
wanting in the beauty of their bodies.</q> <rj><qau>Ray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pule</ent>⟦br⟧
